## What Embeddings Are Good and Bad At

### ✅ Good at (semantic/meaning queries):
- "function that handles user login" → finds auth functions
- "how does payment processing work" → finds payment code
- "class that stores configuration" → finds config classes

### ❌ Bad at (exact identifier queries):
- "executeCode" → might miss because embeddings blur specific tokens
- "REDIS_QUEUE_KEY" → a constant name gets averaged into the vector
- "error on line 42 of utils.py" → too specific for embeddings

**This is exactly why we need BM25 (keyword search) too — Day 4!**

